3 (a) (1) In this section the following words have the meanings indicated.
4 (2) “Developmental delays, physical disabilities, or delays in social,
5 emotional, or behavioral functioning” means:
6 (i) A significant developmental delay or atypical development, as
7 identified by a health professional, in:
8 1. Cognitive development;
9 2. Physical development;
10 3. Language and speech development;
11 4. Psychosocial development; or
12 5. Self–help skills;
13 (ii) Psychological trauma, as identified through an evaluation by a
14 mental health professional; or
15 (iii) A diagnosed physical, developmental, or mental health condition
16 that impacts daily living and limits participation in typical early childhood education or
17 child care settings.
18 (3) “Program” means the Therapeutic Child Care Grant Program.
19 (b) There is a Therapeutic Child Care Grant Program in the State.
20 (c) (1) The purpose of the Program is to provide grants to providers that
21 specialize in providing child care and early childhood education to children under the age
22 of 6 years who have developmental delays, physical disabilities, or delays in social,
23 emotional, or behavioral functioning.
24 (2) The Department shall administer the Program.
25 (3) On or before August 15 each year, the Department shall award grants
26 under this section.
27 (d) (1) For each of fiscal years 2023 through 2025, AND FOR FISCAL YEAR
28 2027 AND EACH FISCAL YEAR THEREAFTER, the Governor shall include in the annual
29 budget bill an appropriation of $3,700,000 to the Program.

